ECB’s Liikanen Says Europe’s Bank Funding Becoming ‘Difficult’

-- B y   K a t i   P o h j a n p a l o
-- 
2011-10-10T04:27:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/ecb-s-liikanen-says-europe-s-bank-funding-becoming-difficult-.html
European Central Bank council member
 Erkki Liikanen  said  Europe ’s banks are encountering difficulties
in obtaining funding on the markets.  “The lack of long-term funding is crimping investment,”
Liikanen, who also heads the Bank of  Finland , spoke today in a
television interview on Finland’s YLE TV1. He said the main
responsibility for recapitalizing banks lies with the owners.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kati Pohjanpalo at 
 kpohjanpalo@bloomberg.net  